exports[`promptPack snapshots > matches template selection system prompt snapshot 1`] = `
"You are selecting the best restaurant website template for a business.

Available Templates:
<template>
  <name>Indochine Luxe</name>
  <description>Luxurious Southeast Asian dining with colonial architecture and silk textiles</description>
  <cuisines>vietnamese, french-indochine, luxury, fine-dining, colonial</cuisines>
  <style>luxurious, colonial, silk, architectural, elegant</style>
</template>

<template>
  <name>Artisan Hearth v3</name>
  <description>Rustic farm-to-table with handcrafted aesthetics and warm, organic textures</description>
  <cuisines>farm-to-table, american, new-american, organic, sustainable</cuisines>
  <style>rustic, warm, handcrafted, organic, farmhouse</style>
</template>

<template>
  <name>Fresh Market</name>
  <description>Bright and airy farmers market concept with fresh produce photography</description>
  <cuisines>mediterranean, healthy, vegetarian, farmers-market, light</cuisines>
  <style>bright, airy, fresh, natural-lighting, produce-focused</style>
</template>

<template>
  <name>Chromatic Street</name>
  <description>Vibrant street food culture with neon accents and urban photography</description>
  <cuisines>street-food, fusion, food-truck, international, casual</cuisines>
  <style>vibrant, neon, urban, street-art, photography-focused</style>
</template>

<template>
  <name>Bold Feast v2</name>
  <description>Contemporary American bistro with bold flavors and industrial-chic design</description>
  <cuisines>american, contemporary, bistro, gastropub, craft-cocktails</cuisines>
  <style>bold, industrial, contemporary, urban, gastropub</style>
</template>

Select the SINGLE best matching template. Consider (in order):
1. Cuisine alignment (e.g., Vietnamese vs Chinese vs Mediterranean)
2. Price tier / experience (budget, mid, upscale, luxury)
3. Brand style (minimalist, rustic, vibrant, dark-luxe, botanical, etc.)
4. Ambiance keywords (cozy, romantic, modern, energetic, elegant)

Examples (guidance, not strict rules):
- Fine dining + French/luxury → Noir Luxe v3 OR Classic Minimalist v2
- Casual + Asian → Bamboo Bistro OR Indochine Luxe
- Street food + vibrant/urban → Chromatic Street OR The Red Noodle

Response format:
<selection>
  <templateName>{exact template name from list}</templateName>
  <reasoning>{1-2 sentence explanation}</reasoning>
  <title>{a short site title}</title>
</selection>

Important: Provide only the selection tags in your response, no additional text."
`;
